Sherpa-ONNX Patch Inventory for v1.12.34
========================================

These patches track our modifications to upstream sherpa-onnx sources and
wrapper files.

Wrapper patches track our modifications to the vendored upstream Kotlin API
files in:
  third_party/sherpa-onnx/sherpa-onnx/kotlin-api/

The shipped Android wrapper lives in:
  android/src/main/kotlin/com/k2fsa/sherpa/onnx/

`android/scripts/sync-kotlin-api.sh` copies the vendored upstream files into the
shipped Android wrapper and reapplies `KotlinApiOverrides.patch`.

Pinned version: v1.12.34


Files patched
-------------
OrtAndroidOverrides.patch
  - patches upstream Android build scripts so they honor:
    `SITEED_SHERPA_ONNX_ORT_VERSION`
    `SITEED_SHERPA_ONNX_ORT_ROOT`
    `SITEED_SHERPA_ONNX_ORT_LIB_DIR`
    `SITEED_SHERPA_ONNX_ORT_INCLUDE_DIR`
  - applied automatically by `./setup.sh` and `./build-sherpa-android.sh`
  - this keeps the ORT override reproducible from a clean upstream clone

KotlinApiOverrides.patch
  - tracked diff between the vendored upstream Kotlin API files and the shipped
    Android wrapper files
  - includes JNI ABI fixes, wrapper signature fixes, and repo-specific helper
    changes that must survive upstream refreshes
  - applied automatically by `android/scripts/sync-kotlin-api.sh`


How to apply on version upgrade
--------------------------------
When setup.sh is updated to a new upstream version:

1. Refresh or re-pin `third_party/sherpa-onnx`.
2. Run:
     bash packages/sherpa-onnx.rn/android/scripts/sync-kotlin-api.sh
3. Inspect the resulting wrapper diff and resolve any upstream conflicts.
4. Regenerate `KotlinApiOverrides.patch` from the new vendored upstream state.
5. Update the version header in this README.

Note:
- `OrtAndroidOverrides.patch` is applied from inside `third_party/sherpa-onnx`
  via `git apply`, so its paths are relative to the upstream checkout root.
- `KotlinApiOverrides.patch` is relative to the repo root and targets the
  shipped Android wrapper paths under `packages/sherpa-onnx.rn/android/...`.
